title: Vaccination
caption: COVID-19 vaccine allocation and administration within 26 February, 2021 and 5 September, 2021 in Austin, TX.
insights: While the first dose of COVID-19 vaccine was administered on 15 December, 2020, by 5 September, 2021 1546643 doses had been administered to 862864 people where about 86.0% had received full dosage.

Compared to 6 day(s) prior, total allocated doses was up by 0.0%, administered doses was up by 1.0%, number of first dose recipients was up by 1.0% and total number of full dose recipients was up by 1.0% on 5 September, 2021.
